<item>
            <title>[FELIX-517] Replacement of {maven-dependencies} in Include-Resource and Bundle-ClassPath can strip Windows path separators</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-517</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On Windows platforms, when you use &lt;/p&gt;
{maven-dependencies} in a custom Include-Resource instruction like the following:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;Include-Resource&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      additional-resource, {maven-dependencies}
&lt;p&gt;, some-other-resource&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;Include-Resource&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then the Windows path separator can be stripped by the String.replaceAll() method - this could also affect other characters that have special meaning in regexp.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution is to use the Plexus StringUtils.replace() method which supports simple string replacement without using regexp (which isn&apos;t actually required here).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
